      * Follow-up email from Jim Weichel showing non-Physics usage: [[%ATTACHURL%/OSG_Usage_for_Non-Physic_Sciences.pdf][Non-Physics]]

%BLUE% *minutes:*
Ruth asked that Rob Quick be asked to present on LHC operations and ticketing at next month's council meeting. Details of her presentation are in the report.

John McGee reported that there have been issues from the TG user community regarding TG ticketing

Chander's report on satellite proposals calls out type 3 & 4 as being interfaced with the council. There were several questions regarding this on how this would operationally and procedurally be viewed to happen. Would the effort exist in the council? Would delegation to the project be exercised as in the past. In general the document was agreed to be very useful and only need to spell out some of the operational aspects, particularly where the council interface was defined.

Jim gave an overview of the science domain usage. There is a definite increase in non-HEP and non-physices usage. Paul reported this to be about double where it was in the past. This is a very hands on process and expected to happen once a year. Would be good to have charts that pull out all physics, as well as pulling out the major stakeholders. 

%ENDCOLOR%

---+++ Status Report from OSG Council Co-Chairs

   * Doodle Poll for Assigning dates for August OSG Council Face-to-Face Meeting
      * [[http://www.doodle.com/zykgavkaz4dtx7vn][URL for Doodle Poll]]

   * Update on !ExTENCI: Extending Science Through Enhanced National Cyberinfrastructure

Funded for first year at roughly $1M. Looking for early success story. Will leverage applications work involving engage and pegasus (and possibly others) to assure this early milestone. Concern expressed over the use of existing personnel to leverage in the margins and our relative scale to TG for being able to do this in a competitive way. Also noted that the purchase of SUN by ORACLE has an unknown implication to the Lustre component. 

%BLUE% *minutes:*

Poll is up. Need more participation to pick date. Venue will be FNAL.

